{{PH census|2010}}{{PH census|2007}}{{LWUA population data}} \n}}\n\nIn the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, the population of Buenavista, Guimaras, was {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people,{{PH census|current}} with a density of {{convert|{{sigfig|{{PH wikidata|population_total}}/{{PH wikidata|area}}|2}}|PD/km2|disp=or}}.\n\n==Transportation==\n[[File:Buenavista Guimaras ferry terminal from pump boat.jpg|thumb|Buenavista,Guimaras ferry terminal from [[pump boat]]]]\nThere are passenger ferries, utilizing [[pump boat]]s to [[Iloilo City]].  The ferry terminal in Iloilo is on the [[Iloilo River]].\n\n==Education==\nBuenavista is the center of higher education. In fact, the main campus of [[Guimaras State College]], only state college in Guimaras, is found in Barangay Mclain. Furthermore, the municipality has 19 public elementary schools, 5 public high schools, and 1 vocational technical school.<ref name=profile/> It has a literacy rate of 98.4%, the highest in the whole of Guimaras.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120413163013/http://nap.psa.gov.ph/activestats/psgc/default.asp Philippine Standard Geographic Code]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081120024509/http://www.census.gov.ph/data/census2007/index.html Philippine Census Information]\n\n{{Geographic location\n| Centre    = Buenavista\n| North     = [[Zarraga, Iloilo|Zarraga]] / [[Dumangas, Iloilo]]<br>''[[Iloilo Strait]]''\n| East      = ''[[Guimaras Strait]]''\n| South     = [[San Lorenzo, Guimaras|San Lorenzo]]\n| Southwest = [[Jordan, Guimaras|Jordan]]\n| West      = [[Iloilo City]] / ''[[Iloilo Strait]]''\n| Northwest = [[Leganes, Iloilo]] / ''[[Iloilo Strait]]''\n}}\n{{Metro Iloilo-Guimaras}}\n{{Guimaras}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of Guimaras]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Municipality of the Philippines in the province of Guimaras}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                   = {{PH wik